OL,3,CGuernsey pupils are more active than
OL,4,CUK students
OL,6,FA survey has revealed that children in
OL,7,Fthe Bailiwick of Guernsey are more
OL,8,Factive than those in the United
OL,9,FKingdom.
OL,11,FAround 789 students from 11 Bailiwick
OL,12,Fprimary schools were surveyed through
OL,13,Fa fitness tracker called a 'Moki'.
OL,15,FThe faceless bracelet measured the
OL,16,Factivity of pupils from Years 3
OL,17,Fthrough 6 for two to three days.
OL,19,FThe trackers revealed that the
OL,20,FBailiwick's children are 23% more
OL,21,Factive than their UK counterparts.
