OL,3,CGuernsey pupils are more active than
OL,4,CUK students
OL,6,FIn a breakdown, female pupils in
OL,7,FGuernsey were 26% more active than UK
OL,8,Ffemale students; 22% of Bailiwick male
OL,9,Fpupils were more active.
OL,11,FThe average step count in Guernsey
OL,12,Fschools ranged from 6000 to 8200
OL,13,Fsteps, while UK schools showed 4000 to
OL,14,F8000 steps.
OL,16,FThe Be Active team at the Health
OL,17,FImprovement Commission conducted the
OL,18,Fstudy to investigate school activity
OL,19,Flevels.
